    {"question": "How does leveling up work in D&D 5e?", "answer": "In D&D 5e, characters level up by gaining experience points (XP) from completing quests, defeating monsters, and overcoming challenges. When a character reaches a certain XP threshold, they gain a level, which typically grants new abilities, increased hit points, and sometimes ability score improvements or feats."},
    {"question": "What are the different types of magic in D&D?", "answer": "In D&D 5e, there are several types of magic, including Arcane (used by wizards, sorcerers, and warlocks), Divine (used by clerics and paladins), and Nature (used by druids and rangers). Each type has its own source of power and spell list."},
    {"question": "How does combat work in D&D 5e?", "answer": "Combat in D&D 5e is turn-based and uses a system of initiative to determine the order of actions. On their turn, characters can move and take one action, such as attacking, casting a spell, or using an item. The outcome of attacks and other actions is determined by rolling dice and adding relevant modifiers."},
