    {"question": "What is the Armor Class (AC) in D&D 5e?", "answer": "Armor Class (AC) in D&D 5e represents how difficult it is to hit a character with an attack. It's determined by the type of armor worn, Dexterity modifier, and sometimes other bonuses. An attacker must roll equal to or higher than the target's AC to land a hit."},
